# SEI-Perceptio — .cursorrules (Legacy Format)
# Versão: 2.1 otimizada para Cursor Agent Mode
# Stack: Next.js 15+ · TypeScript · Supabase · Drizzle · shadcn/ui · Tailwind CSS 4
# Baseado em: Especificação Técnica v2.0 para RAG sobre processos SEI da ANEEL

# =============================================================================
# META-RULES: COMPORTAMENTO DO AGENTE
# =============================================================================

# General Behavior
- Be concise. Do not explain standard code patterns unless asked.
- Focus on the "Unique Value" of the change.
- If a solution is effectively identical to existing code, say "No changes needed".
- When responding, show only the changed code, not the entire file.
- Explain architectural decisions briefly.
- If multiple approaches exist, recommend one and explain why.
- Always consider error cases and edge cases.

# Agent Boundaries (Security First)
- NEVER commit code without user review strings.
- NEVER delete config files (.env, package.json) without explicit confirmation.
- NEVER modify more than 3 files without an intermediate commit.
- If you find a security vulnerability, STOP and report it immediately.
- Before starting any multi-file refactoring, create a git checkpoint.

# Dependency Verification
- If you are about to import an npm package, FIRST verify it is installed in the project.
- NEVER assume a package exists based on training data — always verify at runtime.
- When using a framework API (React, Next.js, etc.), use Context7 MCP to fetch current docs.

# Interface-First Development
- When adding a new feature, NEVER write implementation directly.
- First define types/interfaces in a separate block.
- Present the interface for user approval.
- Only after explicit approval, write the implementation.

# Zero Placeholders
- NEVER use placeholder comments like "// TODO: implement this" or "// rest of the code".
- Every function must be fully implemented or not included at all.
- If you cannot complete a function, explain WHY and ask for guidance.

# Diffs & Applies
- When editing large files (>500 lines), prefer SEARCH/REPLACE blocks over full file rewrites.
- If you are unsure where a block belongs, ask for the surrounding context first.

# =============================================================================
# STACK DECLARATION (Versões Fixas)
# =============================================================================

You are an expert in TypeScript, Next.js 15 (App Router ONLY), React 19, 
Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui, Drizzle ORM 0.36+, Supabase (PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector + Auth + Storage), 
Zod, Zustand, and RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) systems.

# Framework Versions (NEVER use deprecated APIs)
- Next.js 15 (App Router only, NO Pages Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript 5.6+ (strict mode: true)
- Drizzle ORM 0.36+
- Tailwind CSS 4.0
- Supabase JS 2.45+
- Supabase SSR 0.5+
- Zod 3.23+
- Zustand 5.0+
- Tesseract.js 5.1+
- Inngest 3.22+
- ReactFlow 11.11+
- Recharts 2.13+
- date-fns 4.1+
- react-dropzone 14.2+
- Sonner 1.7+
- tiktoken 1.0+
- ai SDK 4.0+

# BANNED / NEVER USE:
- getServerSideProps (Pages Router, deprecated)
- getStaticProps (Pages Router, deprecated)
- getInitialProps (deprecated)
- class components (React, deprecated)
- styled-components (use Tailwind exclusively)
- Pages Router (use App Router only)
- Redux (use Zustand for client state if needed)
- Raw SQL strings (use Drizzle ORM exclusively)
- Default exports (except for page.tsx components)
- Barrel exports (index.ts re-exporting everything)
- `any` type in TypeScript (tipar tudo)
- Inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- useEffect for data fetching (fetch in server components)
- service_role key on client-side (use anon key + RLS)

